result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant shall not consume alcohol or other intoxicants.  Defendant must maintain absolute sobriety.

Case called with 15CT164.  Robert Barrington appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in person, with AttorneyJaclyn Shelton. Ct. reviewed  CPR and PQWOR. Defendant pleads Guilty to OWI-3rd.  Court found plea(s) given FKVI, accepted plea(s), and finds Def. guilty of the charge(s). Ct. found factual basis.  BAC was .20%.  State heard.   Defense heard. 
Court sentenced as follows:  
Based upon her plea in 15CT164, 15CM333 is DRI.  
The PAC charge in 15CT164, is DRI.  
Defendant is sentenced to 18 mos. probation 
24 days in the DCJail with H/T comm. 11-14-15 by 6:00 PM
AODA/VIP w/in 120 days
Fine of $1,800 plus costs, fees, and surcharges
Alcohol Court to commence 10-1-2015 at 3:00 PM
30 mos. revocation/30 mos. IIL

9:07 - Defendant Dawn A. Patzer in court with attorney Jaclyn R. Shelton.  James T. Sempf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant has received copy of Criminal Complaint and advised of rights, charges and penalties. Court finds probable cause. RD & JT set. Court sets $500 PA bond with conditions:   Defendant shall not consume alcohol or other intoxicants.  Defendant must maintain absolute sobriety.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 14, 2015 at 11:15 am.
